        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2019-12-08 13:04:10.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nWhy you abandoned the previous commit https://gerrit.onap.org/r/c/ccsdk/cds/+/96920 ?\nWe had already another commit based on that https://gerrit.onap.org/r/c/demo/+/98996 and it was merged too fast by Marco. Any way work continues in https://gerrit.onap.org/r/c/demo/+/99203",
        "patchset_number": 1
      },
      {
        "id": "f5f178f575bf2c6795df8d5b972ba964f73244c8",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 4567,
          "name": "Yuriy Malakov",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "yuriy.malakov@att.com",
          "username": "ym9479"
        },
        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2019-12-08 13:15:21.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nSamuli, There are additional packages that will be done based on the work that Rashmi is doing to support modifyConfig LCM Action within the vFW CBA Package. Abdel patch is the el Alto version and follow up enhnacement will be made at later point.",
        "patchset_number": 1
      },
      {
        "id": "2e9ef93c101038cfeb2d9ec36d36ad75efc91292",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 3957,
          "name": "Samuli Silvius",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "s.silvius@partner.samsung.com",
          "username": "silvius"
        },
        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2019-12-08 17:41:20.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\n> Patch Set 1:\n> \n> Samuli, There are additional packages that will be done based on the work that Rashmi is doing to support modifyConfig LCM Action within the vFW CBA Package. Abdel patch is the el Alto version and follow up enhnacement will be made at later point.\n\nOk. Rashmi's work is not visible in git? Is all modifications coming to this same CBA? We don't know yet wheather k8s support in this demo can be added to same CBA or do we need to create own CBA for it. \n\nIt feels strange to me (in longer term) if onap content (cba models) are kept within same git repo as platform code. With this logic also all VNF models (csar packages) should be kept in SDC code repository.",
        "patchset_number": 1
      },
